# Frontend Features

When working in `apps/frontend/src/features`, organize code by vertical domain ownership using `src/features/<domain>/modules/<feature>`.
Read `apps/frontend/src/features/README.md` for the full feature guidelines before making structural changes.

- **ALWAYS nest feature code inside `<domain>/modules/<feature>/`.** Never place files directly inside `src/features/<domain>/`, and never use a flat `src/features/<domain>/<feature>/` without the `modules/` layer. Even a single-file feature gets its own module folder: `src/features/settings/modules/profile-tab/profile-tab.tsx`, not `src/features/settings/profile-tab/profile-tab.tsx`.
- **Pages belong in `src/routes/`, NOT in features.** Route files import feature components and render them. Features never contain "page" files.
- Keep module-specific components, hooks, queries, schemas, types, utils, tests, and assets inside the owning `modules/<feature>/` folder (for example `modules/<feature>/components/`, `modules/<feature>/hooks/`).
- **Hooks are scoped to where they're needed:** module-level in `modules/<feature>/hooks/` when only that module uses them, domain-level in `<domain>/hooks/` when shared across modules in the domain (for example `features/auth/hooks/use-auth.ts`), global in `src/hooks/` when truly app-wide.
- **No flat files at the domain level** except domain-scoped shared folders (`hooks/`, `listeners/`, `types/`, `constants/`, `utils/`, `store/`).
- Do not add new features as flat `src/features/<feature>` or `src/features/<domain>/<feature>` folders. Always nest them under `modules/`.
- Do not move feature code into global `components`, `hooks`, `utils`, or `types` folders just because of file kind.
- Import another feature through its public root API when available. Avoid deep imports into another feature's internals.
- Add new shared code only when there is a real shared owner. Otherwise keep it colocated with the module that needs it.
- Preserve and update feature root exports when changing public behavior.
- Run the most targeted available checks for the affected feature, then broaden checks when changes cross feature boundaries.

## Structure

```txt
src/features/<domain>/
  modules/
    <feature>/
      <feature>.tsx
      <feature>.test.tsx
      components/
      hooks/
      schemas/
  hooks/        # domain-level shared hooks (e.g. use-auth.ts, use-user.ts)
  utils/        # domain-level shared utils
  store/
  types/
  constants/
```

Use only the folders a domain actually needs. A small domain might have a single module folder.
